HEADWORD: philosophize
<hw>phi*los"o*phize</hw> <pr>(f⟦icr⟧*l⟦ocr⟧s"⟦osl⟧*f⟦imac⟧z)</pr>,
<pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Philosophized</conjf> <pr>(f⟦icr⟧*l⟦ocr⟧s"⟦osl⟧*f⟦imac⟧zd)</pr>;
<pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>hilosophizing</conjf>
<pr>(f⟦icr⟧*l⟦ocr⟧s"⟦osl⟧*f⟦imac⟧`z⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To
reason like a philosopher; to search into the reason and nature of
things; to investigate phenomena, and assign rational causes for their
existence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Man <qex>philosophizes</qex> as he lives. He may
<qex>philosophize</qex> well or ill, but <qex>philosophize</qex> he
must.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Philosophizer</ent>⟦br⟧
